  "title": "Project Drafter",
  "description": "<p><u>Overall Job Objectives</u></p><p>The BIM modeler will work have to support all life cycle of a projects from feasibility study to design and up to as built of industrial buildings and structures. The modeler will work together with Architects/Design manager to make BIM models/drawings in the areas of Structural & Architectural. The modeler will develop BIM Model and generate AutoCAD 2D. The modeler will prepare layouts, sections, elevations, schedules and blow-up details for submission of drawings.</p><p><u>Core Responsibilities</u></p><p>1. Create 3D models using Autodesk Revit/Bentley OBD /ArchiCAD</p><p>2. Ensure models and shop drawings produced to comply with applicable codes, standards, and specifications</p><p>3. Work in accordance with checking procedures in delivering high-quality models, and drawings</p><p>4. Able to understand, create, and amend drawings/ models in BIM software independently</p><p>5. Able to generate required information from the BIM software</p><p>6. Able to identify drafting errors and highlight them to the project team immediately</p><p>7. Work closely with Project Manager & project teams to ensure drawings/models are as per site requirements</p><p><u>Job Specifications</u></p><p>1. Minimum Bachelor’s Degree in Quantity Surveying/Building or equivalent from a recognized University.</p><p>2. Able to read and understand technical drawings for all disciplines</p><p>3. Good communication, interpersonal and collaboration skills</p><p>4. Minimum 2 years of relevant experience.</p>",
